WEBVTT

00:01.370 --> 00:02.980
[Marcus]
I can't believe
this is happening.

00:03.020 --> 00:05.190
Will Freeman
is my offering

00:05.240 --> 00:07.200
to Oakwood Middle School's
Career Fair.

00:07.240 --> 00:10.030
Tomorrow I'm the kid who brings
in the coolest guy ever

00:10.070 --> 00:11.290
- for career day.
- [chuckles]

00:11.330 --> 00:13.070
Everybody's gonna love
my offering.

00:13.120 --> 00:15.510
You know, you got to stop saying
that word--"offering."

00:15.550 --> 00:16.860
It makes me think
that you're gonna, like,

00:16.900 --> 00:19.030
sacrifice me at an altar,
all right?

00:19.080 --> 00:20.510
[Adanowsky's Rock Me]

00:20.560 --> 00:25.130
♪ Rock me,
I want to get down ♪

00:25.170 --> 00:29.310
♪ Rock me,
I want to get down ♪

00:29.350 --> 00:31.050
This is the altar.

00:31.090 --> 00:32.350
No, it's your booth.

00:32.400 --> 00:34.750
It's all about you
and your legendary career

00:34.790 --> 00:36.440
as the coolest musician
of all time.

00:36.490 --> 00:39.010
Marcus, is that
my high-school yearbook picture

00:39.060 --> 00:41.460
inside a glitter peace sign?

00:41.490 --> 00:43.710
You're welcome.
Oh, look.

00:45.670 --> 00:47.850
Kids can stick their head
through and take a picture,

00:47.890 --> 00:49.060
and it's like they're you.

00:49.110 --> 00:50.760
♪ Won't you ride
my runaway sleigh? ♪

00:50.810 --> 00:52.120
Oh, ho, ho, ho, ho.
It's all right, man.

00:52.160 --> 00:54.300
No, I get it.
Totally, it's a cool thing.

00:54.330 --> 00:56.110
I mean, there's pink glitter
in my hair,

00:56.160 --> 00:57.250
a lot of pink glitter.

00:57.290 --> 00:58.990
Have I ever worn
pink glitter in my hair?

00:59.030 --> 01:01.250
This booth's gonna be
the talk of career day.

01:01.290 --> 01:03.690
I mean, just look at
all these other snooze fests.

01:03.730 --> 01:06.080
- Yeah.
- Tax attorney...

01:06.130 --> 01:11.010
pet groomer, architect,
antivirus expert.

01:11.040 --> 01:12.260
What?

01:12.310 --> 01:14.270
Oh, no offense.

01:14.310 --> 01:16.740
I mean, I'm sure your booth
is terrific.

01:16.790 --> 01:19.140
[sighs]
It's not.

01:19.180 --> 01:21.270
All right, well, I'm gonna go
pick up an extension cord

01:21.310 --> 01:22.490
and plug this bad boy in.

01:22.530 --> 01:24.190
Wait.
W-what does that mean?

01:24.230 --> 01:26.230
[sighs]

01:33.150 --> 01:34.540
Hey, how you doing?

01:34.590 --> 01:36.420
This is what I'd look like
if I was a flamboyant Muppet,

01:36.460 --> 01:37.590
you know what I mean?

01:37.640 --> 01:39.300
[chuckles]

01:39.330 --> 01:40.380
Will?

01:40.420 --> 01:42.250
Hey, Liz, hey.

01:42.290 --> 01:44.160
- Hi.
- Hi.

01:44.210 --> 01:46.160
This is my son, Clay.

01:46.210 --> 01:49.080
Clay, what's going on, man?
I'm a big fan of your mom's.

01:52.080 --> 01:54.430
So, um, why are you
at my school?

01:54.480 --> 01:56.830
Oh, I'm setting up
my career booth, yeah.

01:56.870 --> 01:57.870
So you have a kid?

01:57.920 --> 01:59.480
No.
My friend Marcus goes here.

01:59.530 --> 02:01.920
So your friend
in middle school?

02:01.960 --> 02:03.960
Friend--
well, he's my neighbor.

02:04.010 --> 02:05.360
It's--it's complicated.

02:05.400 --> 02:07.190
Will is a songwriter.

02:07.230 --> 02:08.710
Yeah.
You're into music?

02:08.750 --> 02:10.970
Yeah, yeah, I'm into music.
What'd you write?

02:11.020 --> 02:15.280
Well, I, uh--I wrote a song
called Runaway Sleigh.

02:15.330 --> 02:16.770
The Christmas song--
wow, okay.

02:16.800 --> 02:20.160
Well, in that case, congrats
on your one holiday song,

02:20.200 --> 02:22.240
oh, and your complicated
relationship with a child.

02:22.290 --> 02:24.250
You know, you really know
how to pick 'em, Liz.

02:24.290 --> 02:25.680
- Hmm.
- Thanks, man.

02:25.730 --> 02:26.730
Great to meet you.

02:26.770 --> 02:27.900
Wow.
He's funny.

02:27.950 --> 02:29.560
- Yeah.
- Yeah, he's kind of sarcastic.

02:29.600 --> 02:31.560
He's got that thing going on,
a little bit hurtful.

02:31.600 --> 02:33.340
He never likes
anyone I date,

02:33.390 --> 02:36.820
although I guess I was hoping
it would be different with you.

02:36.870 --> 02:38.000
You don't understand.

02:38.040 --> 02:39.870
I'm gonna make
Clay realize

02:39.910 --> 02:42.310
that you are dating
the coolest guy in town.

02:42.350 --> 02:43.570
I hope so.

02:47.360 --> 02:48.360
Coolest guy in town.

02:48.400 --> 02:49.970
Let there be light!

02:50.010 --> 02:51.400
[electricity buzzing]

02:51.450 --> 02:53.320
[man over speaker]
♪ After school one winter day

02:53.360 --> 02:55.760
♪ I came across
a big red sleigh ♪

02:55.800 --> 02:59.280
♪ Broken down on Highway 63

02:59.330 --> 03:00.770
♪

03:00.810 --> 03:02.990
♪ Cursing it
with all his might ♪

03:03.020 --> 03:05.370
♪ A man whose face
I knew on sight ♪

03:05.420 --> 03:06.980
♪ Here we go

03:07.030 --> 03:10.380
[Brett Dennen's Comeback Kid
[That's My Dog]]

03:10.420 --> 03:12.820
♪ Well, maybe
it's the common curse ♪

03:12.860 --> 03:15.730
♪ Maybe things get bad
before they get worse ♪

03:15.780 --> 03:18.300
♪ I don't want
to become someone ♪

03:18.340 --> 03:21.740
♪ Who can't live up
to what I already done, don't ♪

03:21.780 --> 03:23.780
♪ Here comes a comeback

03:23.830 --> 03:26.180
♪ The kid is back,
is back on track ♪

03:26.220 --> 03:29.180
♪ And there goes my hero

03:29.230 --> 03:33.020
♪ He's the underdog,
he's coming out on top, and ♪

03:33.050 --> 03:35.450
[cheers and applause]

03:37.450 --> 03:40.540
[sighs]

03:40.580 --> 03:43.980
Oh, dude!
What are you doing?

03:44.020 --> 03:45.150
What's up, roomie?

03:45.200 --> 03:47.550
Hey, that is a word
I never want to hear

03:47.590 --> 03:48.720
as a 35-year-old man.

03:48.770 --> 03:50.290
"Roomie," stop it.
What are you doing?

03:50.330 --> 03:52.250
What am I doing?
Laurie's over there at Fiona's

03:52.290 --> 03:55.030
having a doula session, which
I'm still not allowed to attend

03:55.080 --> 03:56.290
on account of that fact
that we're not speaking.

03:56.340 --> 03:57.300
It's so unfair.

03:57.340 --> 03:59.040
You hate
her doula sessions.

03:59.080 --> 04:01.300
I can't believe
she's not talking to me yet.

04:01.340 --> 04:04.690
All I did was get super drunk
and then blow

04:04.740 --> 04:08.870
our future baby's college fund
on racist stage illusions.

04:08.920 --> 04:11.090
It's bad. Now that I say it,
it's very bad.

04:11.140 --> 04:13.530
Can we just stop talking
about you for once?

04:13.570 --> 04:15.100
I'm having
an actual crisis.

04:15.140 --> 04:16.580
I met Liz's son,

04:16.620 --> 04:18.710
and I'm telling you right now,
he was super mean to me.

04:18.750 --> 04:20.450
- That's your crisis?
- Yes.

04:20.490 --> 04:22.150
Isn't winning over
the undying love

04:22.190 --> 04:23.890
of middle schoolers
your specialty?

04:23.930 --> 04:25.150
He's different, okay?

04:25.190 --> 04:26.930
Clay is so cool, Andy,

04:26.980 --> 04:29.240
and he met me in front
of this uber-dorky booth

04:29.290 --> 04:31.640
that Marcus made me.

04:31.680 --> 04:32.940
I got to take back
the booth.

04:32.980 --> 04:34.680
Do you hear yourself
sometimes?

04:34.730 --> 04:37.430
I'm gonna make the booth
so awesome, so, so awesome.

04:37.470 --> 04:39.210
And then Clay's gonna think
I'm awesome,

04:39.250 --> 04:41.510
and he's gonna tell his mom,
reaffirming the fact

04:41.560 --> 04:43.170
that I am
the greatest boyfriend ever.

04:43.210 --> 04:44.600
[claps hands]
And then we're gonna
get you a shower,

04:44.650 --> 04:47.130
general hygiene products,
and a furnished one-bedroom,

04:47.170 --> 04:48.960
and my life
will be perfect.

04:49.000 --> 04:50.740
[Laurie screams]

04:50.780 --> 04:52.520
Damn it! The raccoons
are back in the wall.

04:52.570 --> 04:55.140
- I'm gonna get the shovel.
- Those aren't raccoons.

04:55.180 --> 04:56.700
That's my pregnant wife.

04:56.750 --> 04:59.530
And that's the sound she makes
right before I lose a fortune

04:59.580 --> 05:01.530
and 18 years of my life.

05:01.580 --> 05:03.580
It's baby time.

05:05.630 --> 05:07.590
I'll still get the shovel.

05:07.630 --> 05:11.060
And breathe,
and we're having a baby.

05:11.110 --> 05:12.850
Well, you're having a baby,
but I'm assisting,

05:12.890 --> 05:16.290
and once that happens,
I'm gonna be a certified doula.

05:16.330 --> 05:19.510
Right, Pure Moods I
or Pure Moods II?

05:19.550 --> 05:20.940
[groans]

05:20.990 --> 05:22.160
Both? Both? Both?
Yes, both.

05:22.210 --> 05:23.250
Is it happening?

05:23.300 --> 05:24.780
Oh, look, baby,
there's your father.

05:24.820 --> 05:26.820
He spent your college tuition
on racist magic tricks.

05:26.860 --> 05:28.210
After your mommy tricked me

05:28.260 --> 05:29.300
out of going to magic school
and following my dreams.

05:29.350 --> 05:30.570
Your mommy's
a dream murderer.

05:30.610 --> 05:32.300
Hey, hey, don't say that!
No, no, no, no.

05:32.350 --> 05:34.390
You've got to use
lovely, positive words

05:34.440 --> 05:36.870
to welcome this baby
into a peaceful space.

05:36.920 --> 05:40.050
Lovely words
like "love" and "harmony"

05:40.090 --> 05:42.400
and "certified doula."

05:42.450 --> 05:45.240
Dream murderer.
Dream murderer.

05:45.270 --> 05:47.670
Get away from my belly.
Ah!

05:47.710 --> 05:49.710
Oh, guys, enough, okay?

05:49.760 --> 05:51.930
I am having
an actual crisis here.

05:51.980 --> 05:54.890
Do 13-year-olds
still like Doritos?

05:56.280 --> 05:57.500
What?

06:00.510 --> 06:02.070
[groans]
Why is this taking so long?

06:02.120 --> 06:04.340
I usually shoot these puppies
right out.

06:04.380 --> 06:06.120
The last time, the doctor
nicknamed my birth canal

06:06.160 --> 06:07.730
"the Slip'N Slide,"
remember?

06:07.770 --> 06:09.080
This baby better not
have inherited

06:09.120 --> 06:10.520
your procrastinator gene.

06:10.560 --> 06:12.000
Me? You're the one
who's genetically incapable

06:12.040 --> 06:13.520
of showing up on time.

06:13.560 --> 06:15.650
- Stop it, stop it.
- Oh, that is so--

06:15.700 --> 06:17.010
No fighting.

06:17.040 --> 06:19.000
The more you fight,
the more stressed Laurie gets,

06:19.050 --> 06:21.220
and the longer it's gonna take
till baby o'clock.

06:21.270 --> 06:22.440
You're baby-blocking me.

06:22.490 --> 06:23.580
I'm not baby-blocking you.

06:23.620 --> 06:24.790
- Get out!
- That--

06:24.840 --> 06:26.370
I'm here.
I'm not going anywhere.

06:26.400 --> 06:27.880
- Get out of my hospital room!
- That's not what I meant.

06:27.930 --> 06:29.940
Okay, fine.
Then I'll curtain-block you.

06:29.970 --> 06:31.670
- What?
- No, don't curtain Daddy.

06:31.710 --> 06:33.970
You can't curtain-block me.
I'm right here. Ha ha ha!

06:34.020 --> 06:35.060
- Oh!
- Good-bye.

06:35.110 --> 06:36.060
Still here.

06:36.110 --> 06:37.370
- Out.
- No.

06:37.410 --> 06:38.850
- Huh?
- Give me this curtain.

06:38.890 --> 06:40.020
This is my curtain!

06:40.070 --> 06:41.590
Definitely don't tug-of-war
in mid-labor.

06:41.630 --> 06:42.680
- Her bed's moving!
- [groans]

06:42.720 --> 06:45.550
Stop it!

06:45.600 --> 06:46.650
Oh!

06:49.990 --> 06:52.690
Fine, you win.
I'll be in the waiting room.

06:54.650 --> 06:56.040
Not together.

06:56.080 --> 06:57.870
Suck it.

07:00.520 --> 07:02.740
You took everything down,

07:02.790 --> 07:04.830
even the photo of Sriracha
meeting Paula Abdul.

07:04.880 --> 07:06.760
Look, buddy,
I loved your booth,

07:06.790 --> 07:10.010
but I started to feel like
it was so much about me

07:10.050 --> 07:11.970
and not enough
about songwriting.

07:12.010 --> 07:13.970
I don't know.
It felt like I was showing off.

07:14.010 --> 07:15.840
I think people
would've had a lot of fun

07:15.890 --> 07:18.020
with the Will cutout
strumming the guitar.

07:18.060 --> 07:19.850
I'm sure they would have.
I'm sure they would have.

07:19.890 --> 07:22.890
But you know my motto--
Modesty is the best policy.

07:22.940 --> 07:24.020
I thought your motto was,

07:24.070 --> 07:25.760
"Deep conditioning
isn't just for women."

07:25.810 --> 07:27.720
Well, it isn't,
but, you know,

07:27.770 --> 07:29.680
every man should have
two mottos.

07:29.730 --> 07:30.680
All right.

07:30.730 --> 07:32.380
It is pretty cool

07:32.420 --> 07:35.030
that you brought in all your
guitars just for my career day.

07:35.080 --> 07:36.820
Right?
But listen, this is a big day.

07:36.860 --> 07:37.860
I know it's important
to you.

07:37.910 --> 07:39.520
All right?

07:39.560 --> 07:43.300
What up, my Clayer?
That's "Clay" and "player."

07:43.350 --> 07:44.300
I combined them.
That's what I did.

07:44.350 --> 07:46.130
Yep, mm-hmm, clever.
Hey.

07:46.180 --> 07:48.830
Hey, Marcus, this is
Liz my girlfriend's son.

07:48.880 --> 07:50.100
We have math together.

07:50.140 --> 07:51.960
Oh, right.
Hey, Marvin.

07:53.450 --> 07:55.670
We're not close.

07:55.710 --> 07:58.580
Hey, Clay, you left
your lunch in the car.

07:58.620 --> 08:02.580
Whoa.
Your booth is looking good.

08:02.630 --> 08:03.590
Tell you that, yeah.

08:03.630 --> 08:05.670
Is it?
Analog instruments, really?

08:05.720 --> 08:08.240
Look, all good music nowadays
is electronic, all right?

08:08.290 --> 08:11.810
Calvin Harris, Tiesto, Skrillex,
they're the future.

08:11.860 --> 08:13.610
Well, I love Tiesto.
I mean, they're awesome.

08:13.640 --> 08:14.640
That goes without saying.

08:14.680 --> 08:16.730
Tiesto is one guy.

08:16.770 --> 08:18.160
Yeah, that's what I meant.

08:18.210 --> 08:22.130
I-I said "they" because
I don't believe in gender.

08:27.040 --> 08:28.520
You know what?

08:28.570 --> 08:31.090
I think I put
too much pressure on you.

08:31.140 --> 08:32.710
You guys don't have
to get along.

08:32.750 --> 08:34.280
[sighs]
Oh, man.

08:34.310 --> 08:35.530
I got to go to work.

08:35.570 --> 08:37.490
All right, well, listen,
I got a plan, okay?

08:37.530 --> 08:38.710
- Okay.
- It's a good one.

08:38.750 --> 08:41.710
I'm gonna take care of it all,
all right?

08:41.750 --> 08:43.540
All right, I need a plan.

08:45.980 --> 08:47.890
Hey, thanks for delivering this
on such short notice.

08:47.930 --> 08:49.200
I really appreciate it.

08:49.240 --> 08:51.890
And we appreciate you paying
the $500 rush fee.

08:51.940 --> 08:53.500
Hey, no problem.

08:53.550 --> 08:56.730
If it's going to impress
the coolest kid in school,

08:56.770 --> 08:57.770
it is worth it.

08:57.810 --> 09:00.380
He's even got
a cool-kid name--Clay.

09:00.430 --> 09:02.740
God, I'm intimidated
just saying it.

09:02.780 --> 09:04.960
Tiesto's gonna sound great
on this.

09:05.000 --> 09:06.610
You know,
Tiesto's just one guy.

09:06.650 --> 09:07.820
Okay.

09:09.910 --> 09:11.000
Hey, nice one.

09:11.040 --> 09:12.520
Hey, you guys know
a kid named Clay?

09:12.570 --> 09:15.570
Hey, careful with that.
That's a rental.

09:17.270 --> 09:19.970
Hello, I've recently been
stabbed in the heart

09:20.010 --> 09:22.450
by my best friend
and left in the dust

09:22.490 --> 09:25.410
for his girlfriend's cooler
and more popular son.

09:25.450 --> 09:27.320
Yeah, I feel you.

09:27.370 --> 09:30.420
My girlfriend left me
for a programmer.

09:30.460 --> 09:32.510
Programmers get
all the play.

09:32.540 --> 09:35.020
Mind if I talk to you in
an effort to make him jealous?

09:35.070 --> 09:37.850
As long as you take
a pamphlet,

09:37.900 --> 09:40.380
I don't care
what your motivations are.

09:40.420 --> 09:43.600
Oh, Walter,
you are hilarious!

09:43.640 --> 09:46.780
You have the best booth
at the whole fair,

09:46.820 --> 09:49.780
and I love being
your new best friend

09:49.820 --> 09:51.950
and confidant!

09:52.000 --> 09:54.220
I know
none of this is real.

09:55.520 --> 09:57.660
But it's still
nice to hear.

09:57.700 --> 09:59.830
And since
we're getting close,

09:59.880 --> 10:02.880
I should be honest
with you.

10:02.920 --> 10:06.660
I've never had a girlfriend.
There, I said it.

10:06.710 --> 10:08.800
It feels good
to talk to someone finally.

10:12.980 --> 10:15.240
All right, Laurie,

10:15.280 --> 10:18.630
get ready to be doula'd.

10:22.730 --> 10:24.780
Hi, Laurie.
How you feeling?

10:24.810 --> 10:26.420
Oh, terrible.

10:26.470 --> 10:28.600
I thought Andy being gone
was gonna speed things up.

10:28.640 --> 10:30.780
Oh, dear.
Oh, God.

10:30.820 --> 10:33.870
Oh, look,
Andy left his jacket.

10:33.910 --> 10:36.260
Oh.

10:36.300 --> 10:39.780
Ooh, what's that?

10:39.830 --> 10:42.220
Oh, what is it?

10:42.270 --> 10:46.440
Looks like it's a list
of ways to earn $10,000.

10:46.490 --> 10:47.790
Oh, my God.

10:47.840 --> 10:49.010
He's trying to earn back

10:49.060 --> 10:51.070
the money he blew
on those magic tricks.

10:51.100 --> 10:52.840
[both]
Aw!

10:52.890 --> 10:56.810
And look at the last one that
he circled--"donate plasma."

10:56.850 --> 10:59.020
You know, I did see him
signing some forms

10:59.070 --> 11:00.340
in the waiting room.

11:00.370 --> 11:03.810
Looks like he's willing
to sell part of his body

11:03.850 --> 11:06.290
to provide
for your unborn child.

11:06.330 --> 11:08.810
[both]
Aw!

11:10.340 --> 11:11.860
Oh.

11:11.900 --> 11:13.510
Do you think
he's still out there?

11:13.560 --> 11:16.390
Oh, yeah. No, he's--he's there
sleeping in the waiting room.

11:16.430 --> 11:19.740
He's just going,
"Laurie, Laurie."

11:19.780 --> 11:22.910
I guess if he wanted to come
back in, I'd be okay with it.

11:22.960 --> 11:24.310
Are you sure?

11:24.350 --> 11:26.610
- Yeah.
- Brilliant.

11:26.660 --> 11:28.750
Ooh, and listen,

11:28.790 --> 11:31.750
probably don't mention
the plasma-scheme thing,

11:31.790 --> 11:35.450
'cause you know how men are
with their pride...

11:35.490 --> 11:37.450
about their plasma.

11:37.500 --> 11:38.510
Okay.

11:45.460 --> 11:46.760
Is there a baby?

11:46.810 --> 11:50.200
Oh, no, not yet, no.
It's quite boring in there.

11:50.250 --> 11:51.900
Not a whole lot to doula.
[chuckles]

11:51.940 --> 11:53.990
Laurie's deep in her iPad.

11:54.030 --> 11:56.820
She's looking at magic schools
in Northern California.

11:56.860 --> 11:58.860
She's looking
at magic schools...

11:58.910 --> 12:00.780
because she's trying
to make it up to me.

12:00.820 --> 12:01.780
She wants me back.

12:01.820 --> 12:03.870
Gosh, now you say that,
that--

12:03.910 --> 12:05.300
that does make sense,
doesn't it?

12:05.350 --> 12:06.350
I'm gonna go in there.

12:06.390 --> 12:07.920
Oh, no, wait.
Hold on, hold on.

12:07.960 --> 12:10.440
Because she probably wants it
to be a surprise, doesn't she?

12:10.480 --> 12:12.050
I mean, you don't want her
thinking you're only going

12:12.100 --> 12:14.540
