in the dust.

15:50.700 --> 15:53.050
Marcus,
what is going on, man?

15:53.100 --> 15:56.620
I-I-I'm sorry I didn't hang out
with you today, but--

15:56.670 --> 15:58.320
Okay, you know what?
Just forget it, Will.

15:58.360 --> 16:00.840
I think there's only one thing
left to say to you.

16:02.060 --> 16:03.020
What is that?

16:03.070 --> 16:04.290
I'm giving you
the finger.

16:04.330 --> 16:06.370
That's not
the finger, buddy.

16:06.420 --> 16:07.850
Feel the burn.

16:07.900 --> 16:09.820
That's not it either.

16:09.850 --> 16:11.720
Okay, I get it.
I get it.

16:11.770 --> 16:13.470
I'm stupid at everything,

16:13.510 --> 16:16.030
and Clay probably knows how
to give the finger correctly.

16:16.080 --> 16:17.560
I do.

16:17.600 --> 16:18.990
Yeah, that's it
right there.

16:19.040 --> 16:20.780
Will this nightmare
never end?

16:22.560 --> 16:24.170
I-I got to go talk
to him.

16:24.220 --> 16:25.740
Is he really
your best friend?

16:25.780 --> 16:28.700
Yeah. Like I said,
it's kind of complicated.

16:31.880 --> 16:33.310
I'm so glad you're back.

16:33.360 --> 16:34.440
Me too, honey.
What can I get you?

16:34.490 --> 16:36.310
You want a snack?
Do you want ice chips?

16:36.360 --> 16:37.530
No, no, no. No, thanks.
How about you?

16:37.580 --> 16:38.620
Are you light-headed at all?

16:38.670 --> 16:41.110
